<seg id=1> Fossilized Dinosaur Bones Discovered In Henan Xixia </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Zhengzhou, April 23 (Liu Yaming reporting): Experts have discovered a large amount of fossilized dinosaur bones in Yangcheng Village in Xixia County, which is in the province of Henan. </seg>
<seg id=3> This follows on the valuable discovery of fossilized dinosaur eggs in the region at the beginning of last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> This reporter learned from the Archeological Research Center in Henan province that at the beginning of April of this year researchers working in the gravel beds of two rivers in Yangcheng Town and Hutou Mountain and other places in Xixia County discovered hundreds of dinosaur fossils, including ribs and toes. </seg>
<seg id=5> They've lain exposed on the ground's surface for a long time, so some are already shattered. </seg>
<seg id=6> When looked at from a stratigraphical perspective, they belong to the Cretaceous period. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> According to the experts, there are still a large amount of fossilized dinosaur bones and fossils from other animals buried in the area. </seg>
<seg id=8> They believe that the discovery of such a large amount of dinosaur bones in the Xixia Basin is a rare find, and the fact that the fossilized eggs and bones are in the same place is even more rare. </seg>
<seg id=9> This will have an important impact upon research into Xixia's dinosaurs, investigation of dinosaur ecological and breeding habits, restoration of the environment of the dinosaur age, and revelation of crustal deformation and the evolutionary patterns of the earth's environment. </seg>
<seg id=10> The discovery of the fossilized dinosaur bones offers up important clues in the search for patterns of fossils both on the surface and buried in the ground. </seg>
</p>
